Skepticism by definition has a negative bias it is not objective..

&quot;someone who habitually doubts accepted beliefs&quot;  ( google dictionary )

&quot;skeptical - disbelieving: denying or questioning the tenets of especially a religion; &quot;a skeptical approach to the nature of miracles&quot; 
 ( google dictionary )

&quot;habitually doubts&quot; and &quot;disbelieving&quot; are pretty negative arent they..

The skeptical angle often comes from an assumption that we all can&#39;t be objective because we are &#39;blind believers&#39; not objective observers and so the skeptics just take the counter argument..  

